<TEXT>We test drove the 3.5 and loved the styling. The car handled and had acceptable acceleration but felt heavy. When looking at the weight, I knew that having the 5.0 engine would make all the difference in the world. Well when I went down to test drive it? words can?t describe it. Many people say ?I don?t get it?? I can tell you, get behind the wheel and you ?Will Get It!?. I know it?s not for everyone and honestly, that was a whole level beyond why I wanted it. In the three months I?ve had it, I?ve only seen 3 on the road. I can?t count the FX, ML?s, RX?s, and Cayenne?s. There is a sense of exclusivity that comes with owning one. If you don?t like attention, don?t by an X6. </TEXT>
<FAVORITE>400 horse power and active steering, oh my!</FAVORITE>
